    "name": "Mesh convergence study — non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model to quantify discretization error in predicted construct stiffness and yield force. Four mesh densities (coarse, medium, fine, very-fine) were evaluated using Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2. The Grid Convergence Index (GCI) was computed per Roache (1994) for each quantity of interest. Results indicated GCI < 1.2% for construct stiffness and < 0.9% for yield force at the fine mesh density, which was subsequently adopted as the production mesh. The activity was completed prior to the formal validation comparison and is documented in the FEA Model Verification Report Rev B.",
