      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single displacement rate (25 mm/min) per ASTM F1717 protocol. Only one loading configuration (compression-bending at 5° offset) was evaluated. This single test condition is the primary gap identified in the credibility assessment; achieved level 2 is below the required level 3. Accepted under risk-informed rationale given that ASTM F1717 is the regulatory standard for this device class and clinical loading is predominantly compression-bending."
